snippet.textDisplay:
I don't think Meghan is a bad person, but most predicted her marriage into the royal family would be highly problematic, and here we are. Most expected a divorce, but what's happening now is arguably much worse, since she's the clear catalyst driving a wedge between Harry and his direct family. That being said, if Harry wants to leave, then that's his prerogative.

The main thing that doesn't sit well with me though, is their proposal to only partially leave the royal family. As many are saying, it's like they're trying to have their cake and eat it. With the royals, it should be a case of you're in, or your out. Granted, protection is an issue, but they can afford to sort that out themselves like regular celebrities do, without tax funding coming into it. If they're done being royals, then the taxpayer has every right to be done funding their lavish lifestyle.

snippet.textDisplay:
Interesting to see how British people are reacting to Harry and Megan’s announcement. I am a Canadian and I am delighted that they may wish to spend time here. I hope they will be able to work out the plan they want so that they can live a peaceful, normal life for themselves and Archie. I would be happy to see them remove themselves completely from the FIRM. I would expect and hope that the Canadian press would not harass them as the British media does. Some British media outlets are absolutely cruel, disrespectful, and downright nasty at times - not just with the Royals.  

I am 76 years old and have always been an anti-monarchist. I cannot understand why, in the 21st century, any country on earth still has royalty. After all, they became Royalty as a result of violent wars centuries ago. My own ancestors were booted out of the highlands of Scotland when the British wanted the land for sheep. I am glad they did that because I love living in Canada but it sure was a hardship for my ancestors to be thrown on a ship to a foreign land. Many did not survive. I have visited the UK numerous times. My daughter lived there until recently. It is a wonderful country.

As one of your panel said the Royal Family should be giving back to the public instead of still taking money from them. It is ludicrous that Prince Charles gets so much money from the Duchy of Cornwall. That massive land area and all that the Duchy has control over should be handed over to the public. Let the farmers own the land they work. Let the people own land and help them to build houses there. The money spent on Royals should go to the NHS, public housing, etc. I respect the members of the Royal family as persons but not as Royals. I was pleased that no one in your audience disagreed with Megan and Harry’s plan. The Queen should be much more concerned about Prince Andrew and his behaviour. I subscribe to the Guardian and watch BBC News. Will keep monitoring to see how it goes.
